Pre-Game Insights: Denmark and Sweden are set to face off in a friendly match on June 5, 2024, at the Parken Stadium in Copenhagen.
Denmark qualified for Euro 2024, while Sweden did not.
Denmark has an unblemished defensive record in friendly home games, keeping 11 clean sheets in a row since a 1-1 draw with Germany in June 2017.
Others: The match preview discusses Denmark's qualification for Euro 2024, their defensive record in friendly home games, and Sweden's absence from the tournament.
